const travelWords = [
  w(801,'airport','हवाई अड्डा','a place where planes take off and land','/ˈɛrpɔːrt/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['terminal','aerodrome'],['station','port','harbor'],'I practiced English at the airport while waiting for my flight.','Where is the nearest airport? My flight is in 3 hours.','Airport English = arrivals, departures, check-in, boarding, customs.','Airport announcements require clear, loud, and precise English.','The international airport handled over 60 million passengers annually.','Airport vocabulary: boarding pass, gate, terminal, duty-free, customs!',"Key airport vocabulary: check-in → security → gate → boarding → flight → arrival → immigration → customs → baggage."),
  w(802,'hotel','होटल / आवास','a building where people pay to stay overnight','/hoʊˈtel/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['inn','lodge','resort','hostel'],['home','office','restaurant'],'I stayed in a 3-star hotel during my Mumbai conference.','Can you recommend a good hotel near the railway station?','Hotel English: I\'d like to check in / check out / book a room.','Hotel industry requires exceptional English communication skills.','The hotel provided complimentary breakfast and airport shuttle.','Bro, the hotel was luxurious — breakfast buffet was massive!',"Hotel vocabulary: check-in, checkout, reservation, room service, housekeeping, front desk, concierge."),
  w(803,'ticket','टिकट / परमिट','a piece of paper giving you the right to travel or attend something','/ˈtɪkɪt/','Travel & Transport','noun','A1',['pass','voucher','boarding pass'],['refund','cancellation'],'Book your train ticket at least 2 weeks in advance.','I booked my flight ticket using good English on the airline website.','One return ticket to Delhi please — that\'s all you need to say.','Ticket sales are a primary revenue stream for events and transport.','The airline ticket is non-refundable unless canceled within 24 hours.','Bro, tickets are sold out! We need to book fast!',"'Ticket' (transport), 'ticket' (event entry), 'ticket' (traffic fine). Different contexts, same word."),
  w(804,'journey','यात्रा','a trip from one place to another','/ˈdʒɜːrni/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['trip','travel','voyage'],['destination','arrival','stay'],'The English learning journey is 75 days long.','The journey from Patna to Delhi takes about 12 hours by train.','My English journey began with a single sentence: "Hello, I am..."','The customer journey from awareness to purchase takes multiple touchpoints.','The plaintiff\'s journey to citizenship took over eight years.','Enjoy the journey, not just the destination — wisdom!',"'Journey' = the travel experience. 'Trip' = going and coming back. 'Voyage' = sea. 'Tour' = multiple stops."),
  w(805,'destination','गंतव्य / मंज़िल','the place you are going to','/ˌdestɪˈneɪʃən/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['goal','target','endpoint'],['origin','start','departure'],'Your destination is fluent English — keep going every day.','Paris is my dream travel destination.','The destination of this course: error-free, confident English.','Destination weddings are now a major hospitality market segment.','The flight is bound for its final destination: New York JFK.','Every destination starts with one small step — begin now!',"'Destination' in travel AND in life goals. 'Destination wedding' = popular English term. 'Destination marketing' = tourism field."),
  w(806,'vehicle','वाहन','a machine used to transport people or things','/ˈviːɪkəl/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['car','bus','transport','automobile'],['pedestrian','walker','cyclist'],'What type of vehicle do you use to get to work?','Electric vehicles are the future of sustainable transportation.','Vehicle = the tool. English = the vehicle for expressing your ideas.','The company fleet includes 50 vehicles for logistics operations.','The vehicle was impounded due to expired registration documents.','Bro, vehicle mein toh petrol hi nahi — flat bhi ho gaya!',"'Vehicle' = formal/technical for any transport. Metaphorically: 'language is a vehicle for communication'."),
  w(807,'bus','बस','a large vehicle that carries many passengers','/bʌs/','Travel & Transport','noun','A1',['coach','shuttle','transport'],['car','taxi','bike'],'I take the bus to office every day — eco-friendly choice.','Miss the bus = opportunity gone. Catch the bus = grab the chance.','The bus routes changed — had to Google the English directions.','Company buses for employee transport reduce carbon footprint.','The public bus service was disrupted by the transport workers\' strike.','Miss the bus and wait 30 minutes — learn your English routes!',"'Miss the bus' = miss an opportunity. 'Bustle' = busy movement. 'Business' etymology = busy-ness!"),
  w(808,'train','ट्रेन / गाड़ी','a vehicle that travels on rails','/treɪn/','Travel & Transport','noun','A1',['railway','express','metro','suburban'],['flight','bus','car'],'Indian Railways is one of the world\'s largest train networks.','Take the train to avoid city traffic during peak hours.','On the train I listen to English podcasts — productive commute.','High-speed train networks are transforming regional business connectivity.','The Rajdhani Express train connects Delhi to major cities overnight.','Train journey = best time to read English books — no distractions!',"'Train' = railway vehicle (noun). 'Train' = to teach/practice (verb). 'Training' = practice and development.","train","trains","training","trained","trained"),
  w(809,'flight','उड़ान','a journey by aircraft; a set of stairs','/flaɪt/','Travel & Transport','noun','A1',['airplane ride','trip','air travel'],['landing','ground','arrival'],'My flight to Mumbai departs at 6 AM — need to reach airport by 4.','Book the cheapest flight well in advance for best prices.','Flight mode ON during study = no distractions = maximum focus.','Business class flights offer premium service and productivity space.','The flight was diverted due to severe weather conditions ahead.','Bro, flight of stairs or flight to Dubai — both are flights!',"'Flight' = airplane journey. 'In-flight' = on the plane. 'Flight of stairs' = a set of steps. Multiple meanings."),
  w(810,'hotel check-in','होटल में दाखिल होना','the process of registering at a hotel on arrival','/hoʊˈtel ˈtʃek ɪn/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['registration','arrival','booking'],['checkout','departure','exit'],'At hotel check-in: "I have a reservation under the name Rahul Singh."','Check-in time is usually 2 PM — ask for early check-in if needed.','Hotel English phrases are essential for business travel abroad.','Efficient check-in procedures improve guest satisfaction scores.','The guest was unable to check in due to missing documentation.','Practice these 5 sentences before hotel check-in — feel confident!',"Hotel check-in phrases: 'I have a reservation', 'Can I have a room with..?', 'What time is checkout?'"),
  w(811,'passport','पासपोर्ट','an official document allowing you to travel internationally','/ˈpæspɔːrt/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['identity document','travel document','ID'],['no-ID','anonymous'],'Always check passport expiry before booking international flights.','English is on every passport — learn it to travel the world!','My goal: English fluency + passport = work abroad confidently.','Passport control requires clear and calm communication in English.','The passport must remain valid for at least six months.','Bro, passport stamped in 5 countries! All conversations in English!',"'Passport to success' = the key to achieving something. Passport control = immigration checkpoint."),
  w(812,'visa','वीज़ा','official permission to enter a foreign country','/ˈviːzə/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['permit','entry permission','travel authorization'],['ban','rejection','denial'],'IELTS score of 6.5 is required for a UK visa application.','English proficiency is required for most visa applications.','Visa interviews in embassies require confident English speaking.','Work visa requirements vary significantly by country and profession.','The visa was denied due to insufficient documentation.','English opens visa doors — IELTS, TOEFL, PTE — all in English!',"'Visa on arrival' = get visa when you land. 'E-visa' = online application. 'Transit visa' = passing through."),
  w(813,'luggage','सामान / बैगेज','bags and cases you take when traveling','/ˈlʌɡɪdʒ/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['baggage','suitcase','bags'],['nothing','empty','minimal'],'Travel with light luggage — only take what you need.','My luggage got lost at Mumbai airport — thank god I spoke English!','Pack light on luggage, heavy on vocabulary — travel wisdom.','Airlines charge excess luggage fees for bags over the limit.','The airline was liable for the damaged luggage under consumer law.','Bro, packed 3 bags — cabin crew said max 1 carry-on!',"'Luggage' is uncountable. 'A piece of luggage' = one bag. 'Baggage' = more formal/official term."),
  w(814,'reservation','आरक्षण / बुकिंग','an arrangement to have something kept for you','/ˌrezərˈveɪʃən/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['booking','appointment','hold'],['cancellation','walk-in','rejection'],'I have a reservation at the Taj Hotel for 2 nights.','"I\'d like to make a reservation for 2 people this Saturday evening."','Restaurant reservation — key English phrase for professional dining.','Advance reservations are required for all high-demand business events.','The reservation was confirmed via email with a reference number.','Table for two please — do you have a reservation? Yes, under Singh!',"'Make a reservation' (hotel/restaurant). 'Book' (flights/hotels). 'Reserve' (seats/tables). All related.","reserve","reserves","reserving","reserved","reserved"),
  w(815,'customs','सीमा शुल्क / रीति-रिवाज','government office at a border; traditions and habits','/ˈkʌstəmz/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['immigration','border control','traditions'],['freedom','no restrictions'],'Customs officer asked: "Anything to declare?" — Know this phrase!','Customs and traditions differ across cultures — be respectful.','Cleared customs — finally in London! My first English conversation abroad.','Customs duties affect import costs for international businesses.','The goods were seized by customs officials at the port of entry.','At customs: smile, speak clearly, answer honestly — easy!',"'Customs' (tax department at border) vs. 'customs' (cultural traditions). Same word, very different meanings."),
  w(816,'direction','दिशा / निर्देश','the way you face, move, or point towards something','/dɪˈrekʃən/','Travel & Transport','noun','A1',['way','path','route','guidance'],['wrong way','lost','confusion'],'Can you give me directions to the nearest metro station?','My English learning has found its direction — this course!','North, south, east, west are the four cardinal directions.','Clear directions reduce confusion in project management.','The parties agreed on the direction of the negotiation.','Left, right, straight ahead — key English direction words!',"'Direction' (compass/physical) and 'direction' (guidance/management). 'In the right direction' = making progress."),
  w(817,'arrival','आगमन','the act of reaching a place','/əˈraɪvəl/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['coming','reaching','landing'],['departure','leaving','exit'],'On arrival at the airport, proceed to immigration.','Arrival of the monsoon brings relief from the summer heat.','My arrival to English fluency is 75 days away — I\'m coming!','New employee arrivals must complete onboarding within the first week.','Upon arrival, all passengers must present their boarding pass.','Arrival = beginning of a new chapter — start well!',"'Arrival' (coming). 'Departure' (going). 'Arrival hall' = where you meet people at airport."),
  w(818,'departure','प्रस्थान','the act of leaving a place','/dɪˈpɑːrtʃər/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['leaving','exit','takeoff'],['arrival','return','stay'],'Departure time is 7:30 AM — reach airport by 5:30 AM.','His departure from the company was a great loss to the team.','Our departure from Hindi thinking to English thinking — key shift.','Employee departure (attrition) costs companies 2× the annual salary.','Notice of departure must be given 30 days in advance.','Departure gate B12 — 10 minutes to boarding!',"'Departure from' = leaving (flight departure). 'A departure from tradition' = doing something differently."),
  w(819,'platform','मंच / प्लेटफ़ॉर्म','a raised surface; a place where trains stop; a digital service','/ˈplætfɔːrm/','Travel & Transport','noun','A2',['stage','base','service'],['underground','hidden'],'The Rajdhani departs from platform 3 at 6 PM.','This English course is your platform for a better career.','English is the platform on which global careers are built.','Digital learning platforms are revolutionizing education globally.','The platform economy (Uber, Zomato) has created millions of jobs.','Platform 1 vs. Platform 9¾ — only Harry Potter knows!',"'Platform' = railway (train platform), digital (YouTube platform), politics (party platform = their policies)."),
  w(820,'traffic','यातायात','vehicles moving on roads; web/network usage','/ˈtræfɪk/','Travel & Transport','noun','A1',['vehicles','congestion','flow'],['empty road','peace','clear'],'Mumbai traffic is the worst — use public transport!','Website traffic increased 300% after we added English content.','During traffic jams, I practice English — never waste time.','Organic search traffic is the most valuable for digital businesses.','Traffic regulations are strictly enforced in metropolitan areas.','Stuck in traffic? Perfect time for English podcast listening!',"'Traffic' = vehicles (road traffic), web visitors (web traffic), communication (air traffic control)."),
];

