const foodWords = [
  w(821,'breakfast','नाश्ता','the first meal of the day','/ˈbrekfəst/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['morning meal','brunch'],['dinner','supper','lunch'],'I always eat a healthy breakfast before studying English.','Breakfast meeting at 8 AM — very common in corporate world.','Breakfast vocabulary: toast, oats, eggs, fruit, juice, cereal.','Business breakfast meetings are popular in Western corporate culture.','The hotel provides a complimentary breakfast for all guests.','Skip breakfast, lose focus — always eat before studying!',"'Breakfast' etymology: 'break' + 'fast' = breaking the overnight fast. 'Brunch' = breakfast + lunch combined."),
  w(822,'lunch','दोपहर का खाना','the midday meal','/lʌntʃ/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['midday meal','noon meal'],['breakfast','dinner','supper'],'I have lunch with colleagues and practice English conversation.','Let\'s grab lunch together and discuss the project updates.','Lunch break is my English practice time — 30 minutes daily.','Working lunches are common in fast-paced corporate environments.','The employment contract includes a one-hour paid lunch break.','Lunch > meeting. Can we do both? A working lunch!',"'Lunch' vs. 'Luncheon' (formal). 'Working lunch' = eating while meeting. 'Lunch break' = time off for lunch."),
  w(823,'dinner','रात का खाना','the main meal of the day, usually in the evening','/ˈdɪnər/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['supper','evening meal'],['breakfast','lunch','snack'],'Family dinner time is perfect for English practice conversations.','Dinner with the client went well — great conversation in English.','Business dinners are important for relationship building and deals.','Formal business dinners have specific etiquette rules to follow.','The dinner was held at the five-star hotel for the visiting delegation.','Bro, dinner is ready! Come join us at the table!',"'Dinner' = main meal (usually evening). 'Supper' = light evening meal. 'Banquet' = formal group dinner."),
  w(824,'restaurant','रेस्तराँ','a place where meals are prepared and served to customers','/ˈrestrɒnt/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['eatery','diner','café','bistro'],['home','kitchen','canteen'],'I ordered my meal completely in English at the restaurant.','"Table for two, please" — essential restaurant English phrase.','Restaurant visits helped me practice real English conversations.','Restaurant industry is one of the fastest-growing employment sectors.','The health department inspected the restaurant\'s food storage.','Fine dining restaurant: use proper English table manners!',"Restaurant phrases: 'Table for..?', 'What do you recommend?', 'The bill, please', 'Can we split?'"),
  w(825,'menu','मेनू / सूची','a list of food and drinks available in a restaurant','/ˈmenjuː/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['list','options','card'],['order','receipt','bill'],'May I see the menu please? — Classic restaurant question.','The restaurant menu had both Hindi and English descriptions.','Learn food vocabulary to order confidently from any menu.','Digital menus with QR codes are now standard in restaurants.','The menu featured seasonal ingredients sourced from local farms.','Bro, what\'s on the menu? I\'m starving — anything good?',"'Menu' in restaurants (food list) and tech (dropdown menu). 'Prix fixe' menu = set price for all courses."),
  w(826,'healthy','स्वस्थ / पौष्टिक','good for your body or mind','/ˈhelθi/','Food & Nutrition','adjective','A1',['nutritious','wholesome','fit','beneficial'],['unhealthy','junk','harmful'],'Eat healthy food to keep your brain sharp for learning.','A healthy work-life balance improves overall performance.','Healthy body + healthy mind = optimal English learning capacity.','Companies are investing in healthy snack options at workplaces.','Regular exercise and a healthy diet reduce chronic disease risk.','Healthy eating challenge: 30 days, no junk food. Who\'s in?',"'Healthy' for food (healthy diet), people (a healthy person), business (healthy profits). Very versatile."),
  w(827,'vegetable','सब्जी','a plant or part of a plant used as food','/ˈvedʒtəbəl/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['veggie','greens','produce'],['meat','fruit','junk food'],'Vegetables are the foundation of a nutritious Indian diet.','Do you eat vegetables daily? They are essential for health.','Vegetable vocabulary: spinach, carrot, tomato, onion, potato, peas.','The vegetable supply chain was disrupted during the lockdown.','Organic vegetables command higher prices in premium markets.','Bro, eat your vegetables — your mom knows best!',"'Vegetables' common words: potato (aloo), onion (pyaz), tomato (tamatar), carrot (gajar), spinach (palak)."),
  w(828,'fruit','फल','the sweet part of a plant containing seeds','/fruːt/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['produce','berry','harvest'],['vegetable','meat','processed'],'An apple a day keeps the doctor away — famous English saying.','Fresh fruit for breakfast boosts energy levels for the morning.','Fruit vocabulary: apple, banana, mango, orange, papaya, grapes.','The fruit export business has significant foreign exchange potential.','The court considered the fruits of the labor in calculating damages.','The fruit of your hard work will show on Day 75!',"'Fruit' can be singular/uncountable (eat fruit) or countable (two fruits on the table). Context matters."),
  w(829,'order','आदेश देना / क्रम','to request food or goods; a sequence; a command','/ˈɔːrdər/','Food & Nutrition','verb','A2',['request','arrange','command','direct'],['cancel','refuse','disorder'],'May I order a coffee please? That\'s all you need to say!','I always order the same thing — decision fatigue avoided.','Practice ordering food in English — great first-step conversation.','Order processing time affects customer satisfaction scores significantly.','The court issued an order restraining the defendant from leaving.','Zomato order vs. Amazon order vs. judge\'s order — same word!',"'Order' as verb (order food), noun (in order = organized, out of order = broken/disorganized), legal (court order).","order","orders","ordering","ordered","ordered"),
  w(830,'meal','भोजन','food eaten at a regular time each day','/miːl/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['food','dish','course'],['snack','fast','drink'],'A nutritious meal fuels a productive learning session.','Business meal etiquette is an important professional skill.','Meal prep on Sunday helps me eat healthy all week.','Meal allowance is included in many corporate expense policies.','The meal was prepared according to strict dietary requirements.','Bro, what a meal that was — 10 courses, all amazing!',"'Meal' (formal/general). 'Dish' (specific preparation). 'Course' (part of a meal: starter, main, dessert)."),
  w(831,'cook','खाना बनाना / रसोइया','to prepare food using heat; a person who prepares food','/kʊk/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['chef','prepare','make'],['eat','serve','buy'],'I cook simple English food to practice recipe vocabulary.','The company cook prepares 500 meals daily for employees.','Cooking shows in English improved my food vocabulary greatly.','Professional cooks and chefs require strong technical vocabulary.','The head cook was responsible for ensuring food safety compliance.','I can cook daal-chawal and scrambled eggs — survival skills!',"'Cook' = informal, basic cooking. 'Chef' = professional cook. 'Baker' = bread/pastry specialist.","cook","cooks","cooking","cooked","cooked"),
  w(832,'taste','स्वाद / चखना','the sensation in your mouth from food; to test food','/teɪst/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['flavor','savor','relish'],['tasteless','bland','odorless'],'English vocabulary has so many taste words — sweet, sour, bitter.','Taste is subjective — what one person loves, another may not.','Taste the food vocabulary: sweet, sour, salty, bitter, spicy, savory.','Brand taste tests help companies understand consumer preferences.','The taste of food is affected by its temperature, texture, and aroma.','Bro, taste this! Rate it: sweet, spicy, or bland?',"Taste words: sweet (मीठा), sour (खट्टा), salty (नमकीन), bitter (कड़वा), spicy (तीखा), bland (फीका).","taste","tastes","tasting","tasted","tasted"),
  w(833,'drink','पीना / पेय','to consume liquid; a beverage','/drɪŋk/','Food & Nutrition','verb','A1',['beverage','sip','consume','have'],['eat','fast','abstain'],'Drink 8 glasses of water daily for optimal brain function.','What would you like to drink? Tea, coffee, or water?','I drink green tea while studying — it keeps me focused.','Non-alcoholic drink options must be available at all business events.','Drinking clean water remains a challenge in many parts of the world.','Drink to that! — English way of celebrating with a toast!',"'Drink' past = 'drank', past participle = 'drunk'. 'Drink' (non-alcoholic) vs. 'have a drink' (could be alcohol).","drink","drinks","drinking","drank","drunk"),
  w(834,'coffee','कॉफ़ी','a hot drink made from roasted coffee beans','/ˈkɒfi/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['espresso','cappuccino','latte'],['tea','juice','water'],'I drink one coffee every morning before English study.','Coffee meeting = informal business discussion over coffee.','Coffee break in office = informal English conversation opportunity.','The global coffee market is worth over $100 billion annually.','The plantation workers filed a complaint against the coffee company.','Coffee is life — but too much caffeine kills focus!',"Coffee vocabulary: espresso (strong shot), cappuccino (espresso + foam), latte (espresso + milk), americano (espresso + water)."),
  w(835,'tea','चाय','a hot drink made by adding water to dried tea leaves','/tiː/','Food & Nutrition','noun','A1',['herbal tea','chai','brew'],['coffee','juice','soda'],'I prefer green tea over coffee for studying English.','Tea time = British tradition = perfect conversation starter.','Not my cup of tea = English idiom meaning not my preference.','The Indian tea industry employs over a million workers.','The tea estate was the subject of a prolonged legal dispute.','Bro, chai break! Let\'s discuss today\'s lesson over tea!',"'Not my cup of tea' = I don\'t like it. 'Tea' is UK\'s national drink. 'Chai' = Indian tea. Both perfect!"),
  w(836,'spicy','तीखा / मसालेदार','having a strong, hot flavor from spices','/ˈspaɪsi/','Food & Nutrition','adjective','A2',['hot','fiery','pungent','peppery'],['mild','bland','plain'],'Indians love spicy food — and we love English too!','This curry is too spicy — can you make it milder please?','Spicy vocabulary: pungent, zesty, fiery, tangy — all mean intense flavor.','Spicy food challenges are popular content on social media.','The health benefits of spicy food include improved metabolism.','Bro, this biryani is fire! — Spicy, not literally fire!'),
  w(837,'sweet','मीठा','having the taste of sugar; kind and pleasant','/swiːt/','Food & Nutrition','adjective','A1',['sugary','dessert','honey','pleasant'],['bitter','sour','salty'],'Success tastes sweet only after hard work.','Sweet talks in negotiations — be careful of manipulation.','My sweet spot for English learning: 7-9 PM daily.','Sweet words alone don\'t build trust — actions do in business.','The dessert was too sweet — three teaspoons of sugar too many.','That\'s sweet of you — English phrase for expressing appreciation!',"'Sweet' = taste (sweet mango), personality (she\'s so sweet), idioms (sweet dreams, sweet spot, home sweet home)."),
  w(838,'bitter','कड़वा','having a sharp, unpleasant taste; feeling resentful','/ˈbɪtər/','Food & Nutrition','adjective','A2',['sour','sharp','acrid'],['sweet','pleasant','mild'],'Coffee is bitter — but it keeps you focused for studying.','Don\'t be bitter about failures — learn and move forward.','Bitter truth is better than a sweet lie — wisdom saying.','Leaving a bitter customer experience affects brand loyalty.','The trial left both parties bitter and financially exhausted.','Bitter experience = best teacher. English truth!',"'Bitter' (taste), 'bitter' (resentful emotion), 'a bitter pill to swallow' = accepting something difficult."),
  w(839,'fresh','ताज़ा','recently made or obtained; new and clean','/freʃ/','Food & Nutrition','adjective','A1',['new','clean','crisp','recent'],['stale','old','expired','rotten'],'Fresh vocabulary learned today — never forget it with revision.','Start fresh every morning — yesterday\'s mistakes are lessons.','Fresh ideas make your business communication stand out.','Fresh produce must be stored at optimal temperatures.','Fresh evidence emerged that changed the entire course of the trial.','Fresh start Monday — new week, new English goals!',"'Fresh' = new/recent (fresh idea), clean/cool (fresh air), bold (don\'t be fresh = rude in old American English)."),
  w(840,'delicious','स्वादिष्ट','having a very pleasant taste or smell','/dɪˈlɪʃəs/','Food & Nutrition','adjective','A1',['tasty','yummy','scrumptious'],['awful','terrible','disgusting'],'This dal tadka is absolutely delicious!','The client dinner was delicious — great impression made.','English is delicious — every new word is a treat!','Delicious food photography drives engagement on restaurant social media.','The Michelin-star meal was described as truly delicious by critics.','Bro, this food is so delicious — tell me the recipe!',"'Delicious' = tastes great. 'Yummy' = informal/child-like. 'Scrumptious' = very informal/funny. 'Delectable' = formal."),
];

