const techWords = [
  w(841,'technology','तकनीक','the use of science in practical ways, especially machines and computers','/tekˈnɒlədʒi/','Technology','noun','A2',['tech','innovation','digital','machinery'],['nature','manual','traditional'],'Technology is transforming English education globally.','My company uses the latest technology to serve clients better.','Technology skills + English skills = unstoppable combination!','Technology investment drove the company\'s digital transformation.','Technology regulation is becoming a critical area of public policy.','Bro, technology has made learning English so much easier!',"'Technology' (broad/abstract). 'Tech' (informal). 'Gadget' (specific device). 'Innovation' (new technology)."),
  w(842,'computer','कंप्यूटर','an electronic device that processes and stores data','/kəmˈpjuːtər/','Technology','noun','A1',['laptop','PC','desktop','device'],['manual','typewriter','paper'],'I practice English typing on my computer every day.','Computer literacy is required for most modern job roles.','My computer has 20 English learning apps installed!','Computer skills are mandatory for all administrative positions.','The computer store all court records and case documentation.','Bro, my computer crashed — 2 hours of English work gone!',"'Computer' = desktop/laptop. 'PC' = personal computer. 'Mac' = Apple computer. 'Laptop' = portable computer."),
  w(843,'internet','इंटरनेट','the global network connecting computers worldwide','/ˈɪntənet/','Technology','noun','A1',['web','online','network','WiFi'],['offline','disconnect','manual'],'The internet gave me access to unlimited English resources.','No internet = no problem. Download content and study offline.','Internet English is different from formal written English — know both.','Internet penetration in India reached 900 million users in 2024.','Internet service providers are regulated under telecom laws.','No WiFi no life? Wrong — downloaded lessons work offline!',"'Internet' vs. 'web': Internet = the network. Web (World Wide Web) = content on the internet."),
  w(844,'smartphone','स्मार्टफोन','a mobile phone with computer capabilities','/ˈsmɑːrtfoʊn/','Technology','noun','A1',['mobile','phone','device','handset'],['laptop','computer','tablet'],'My smartphone is my English learning companion 24/7.','Smartphone vocabulary: app, notification, screen, tap, swipe, zoom.','Use your smartphone for English podcasts during commute.','Smartphone adoption in rural India is driving EdTech growth.','The defendant\'s smartphone data was admitted as evidence.','Bro, phone toh mere haath mein hi rehta hai — English practice on!'),
  w(845,'application','आवेदन / एप्लिकेशन','a program for a device; a formal request','/ˌæplɪˈkeɪʃən/','Technology','noun','A2',['app','program','software','form'],['uninstall','removal','rejection'],'Download the English learning app and practice 30 min daily.','Submit your application for the job before the deadline.','Application = job form AND mobile app — very different contexts.','Application development is one of the fastest-growing tech careers.','The visa application requires supporting documents and correct forms.','App store has 3 million apps — choose wisely!',"'Application' = app (tech), job application (HR), college application (education). Three very different contexts."),
  w(846,'password','पासवर्ड','a secret word used to access a system','/ˈpæswɜːrd/','Technology','noun','A1',['PIN','code','access key'],['public','open access','transparent'],'Create strong passwords with capital letters, numbers, symbols.','Never share your password with anyone — basic security rule.','My password to success: practice English every single day.','Password managers help employees securely store access credentials.','The defendant claimed not to remember the email account password.','Password: 75DaysHardEnglish2026! — 100% secure and motivating!',"Strong password tips: 12+ characters, mix letters/numbers/symbols, no personal info. Use a password manager."),
  w(847,'data','डेटा / जानकारी','facts and statistics collected for analysis','/ˈdeɪtə/','Technology','noun','A2',['information','facts','statistics'],['opinion','guess','estimate'],'Data shows that daily practice improves fluency 3x faster.','Your learning data is tracked automatically in the dashboard.','Data-driven decisions are the backbone of modern businesses.','Big data analytics provides insights into customer behavior patterns.','Data privacy laws require explicit consent before data collection.','Your phone knows more about you than your best friend — data!',"'Data' is technically plural (singular: datum) but commonly treated as singular. 'Data is' = American. 'Data are' = formal."),
  w(848,'software','सॉफ़्टवेयर','programs and operating systems for computers','/ˈsɒftweər/','Technology','noun','A1',['program','app','platform','tool'],['hardware','device','physical'],'This English learning software adapts to your learning pace.','Our company uses advanced software for project management.','Software skills are as important as language skills today.','Software as a Service (SaaS) dominates enterprise tech solutions.','The software license agreement was reviewed by the legal team.','Software update available — download for new English content!',"'Software' (programs) vs. 'Hardware' (physical devices). 'Firmware' = embedded software. All uncountable nouns."),
  w(849,'website','वेबसाइट','a set of pages on the internet with related information','/ˈwebsaɪt/','Technology','noun','A1',['site','web page','portal'],['book','magazine','offline'],'Visit our website for free English practice materials.','A professional website builds credibility for your business.','I visit 5 English learning websites daily for variety.','Website traffic, bounce rate, and conversions are key metrics.','The website terms and conditions constitute a binding agreement.','Bro, the website design is fire — clean, fast, professional!',"'Website' = whole site. 'Web page' = one page on the site. 'Portal' = gateway with multiple services."),
  w(850,'digital','डिजिटल','using computer technology; not physical/analog','/ˈdɪdʒɪtəl/','Technology','adjective','A2',['electronic','online','virtual','tech'],['physical','analog','manual','offline'],'Digital English learning is flexible and personalized.','Digital transformation is reshaping every industry globally.','Digital fluency + English fluency = future-proof career.','Digital marketing is now the primary channel for business growth.','Digital evidence is increasingly relevant in modern legal proceedings.','Digital world needs digital skills — and English is No. 1!',"'Digital native' = someone born into the digital age. 'Digital divide' = gap between tech-haves and have-nots."),
  w(851,'update','अपडेट करना / सुधारना','to make something more modern or current','/ʌpˈdeɪt/','Technology','verb','A2',['upgrade','refresh','renew','improve'],['downgrade','ignore','delete'],'Update your vocabulary list daily with new words learned.','Please update the client on the project progress by email.','I update my English skills by learning 20 new words daily.','Regular status updates keep stakeholders informed and confident.','The law must be updated to address new digital crime challenges.','Update available: 10 new vocabulary words — download now!',"'Update' (tech: software update), 'update' (communication: keep updated = inform regularly). Both very common.","update","updates","updating","updated","updated"),
  w(852,'download','डाउनलोड करना','to copy data from the internet to your device','/ˈdaʊnloʊd/','Technology','verb','A2',['save','install','retrieve'],['upload','delete','remove'],'Download the English study materials and practice offline.','Download all lessons — use them even without internet.','Downloading podcasts = English practice anywhere, anytime.','The report can be downloaded as a PDF for easy sharing.','Downloading copyrighted material without permission violates the law.','Download it now before you forget — free resources go fast!',"'Download' (receive data from internet). 'Upload' (send data to internet). Both essential digital vocabulary.","download","downloads","downloading","downloaded","downloaded"),
  w(853,'upload','अपलोड करना','to copy data from your device to the internet','/ʌpˈloʊd/','Technology','verb','A2',['share','post','send','submit'],['download','delete','remove'],'Upload your English speaking recording for feedback.','Please upload all documents to the shared folder.','I upload my English practice videos to track progress.','Users can upload content directly to the learning platform.','The video evidence was uploaded to the court\'s digital system.','Upload your work and get instant AI feedback — amazing technology!',"'Upload' (send to cloud/server). 'Download' (receive from cloud). 'Cloud storage' = online storage service.","upload","uploads","uploading","uploaded","uploaded"),
  w(854,'search','खोजना','to look carefully for something, especially online','/sɜːrtʃ/','Technology','verb','A1',['look up','find','query','browse'],['ignore','miss','overlook'],'Search any English word online and learn it immediately.','Google something you don\'t know — that\'s modern learning.','I search for English examples of words before using them.','Search engine optimization (SEO) drives organic website traffic.','The search warrant allowed investigators to seize digital devices.','Google it! That\'s the answer to 90% of English questions.',"'Search' vs. 'research': Search = find specific info quickly. Research = systematic, in-depth investigation.","search","searches","searching","searched","searched"),
  w(855,'social media','सोशल मीडिया','online platforms where people share content and interact','/ˈsoʊʃəl ˈmiːdiə/','Technology','noun','A2',['Facebook','Instagram','LinkedIn'],['newspapers','books','face-to-face'],'Use social media in English to practice writing daily.','LinkedIn is the social media platform for professional networking.','Social media helped me connect with English speakers worldwide.','Social media marketing is now 50% of total ad spend globally.','Social media evidence is increasingly used in court proceedings.','LinkedIn English vs. Instagram English = very different styles!',"'Social media' uncountable. Types: professional (LinkedIn), visual (Instagram), microblogging (Twitter/X), video (YouTube)."),
  w(856,'email','ईमेल','electronic message sent online','/ˈiːmeɪl/','Technology','noun','A1',['e-mail','message','correspondence'],['letter','call','chat'],'Professional email writing is the most used English skill today.','Cc = carbon copy. Bcc = blind carbon copy. Know these terms.','Email etiquette: clear subject, professional tone, proper closing.','Average professional receives 121 emails daily — write clear ones.','Email evidence was presented as exhibit A in the court case.','Subject line is the most important part of any email — master it!',"Email structure: Subject line | Greeting | Opening | Body | Closing | Signature. Always proofread.","email","emails","emailing","emailed","emailed"),
  w(857,'video call','वीडियो कॉल','an online meeting where you can see each other','/ˈvɪdioʊ kɔːl/','Technology','noun','A2',['video conference','Zoom','Teams'],['phone call','text','email'],'Video call English needs clear pronunciation and loud voice.','All team meetings are now via video call — English is a must.','Video call tips: look at camera, speak clearly, minimize background noise.','Remote work increased video call usage by 500% globally.','Video call evidence must meet authentication standards in court.','Mute yourself when not speaking on video calls — basic etiquette!',"Video call platforms: Zoom, Microsoft Teams, Google Meet, Cisco Webex. All require clear English."),
  w(858,'password reset','पासवर्ड रीसेट','the process of creating a new password','/ˈpæswɜːrd riːset/','Technology','noun','A2',['account recovery'],['login','access'],'Forgot password? Password reset email sent to your inbox.','Password reset is the second most common IT support request.','English IT vocabulary: reset, account, verify, authenticate.','IT help desks handle thousands of password reset requests daily.','Account recovery procedures are documented in the security policy.','Forgot password = most relatable digital problem in the world!',"Password security: never reuse passwords, use 2FA (two-factor authentication), change every 90 days."),
  w(859,'artificial intelligence','कृत्रिम बुद्धिमत्ता','computer systems that can perform tasks requiring human intelligence','/ˌɑːrtɪˈfɪʃəl ɪnˈtelɪdʒəns/','Technology','noun','B1',['AI','machine learning','automation'],['human intelligence','manual','natural'],'AI is now helping millions learn English more effectively.','AI tools like ChatGPT can help you practice English 24/7.','AI + Human effort = fastest path to English fluency.','AI is transforming recruitment, customer service, and education.','AI regulation is the most pressing technology policy challenge today.','AI helps, but consistency is still up to you — choose wisely!',"'AI' = Artificial Intelligence. 'ML' = Machine Learning (subset of AI). 'GenAI' = Generative AI (like ChatGPT)."),
  w(860,'cloud','क्लाउड / बादल','internet-based storage and computing; condensed water vapor in sky','/klaʊd/','Technology','noun','A2',['cloud storage','sky','server','online'],['local storage','physical','on-premise'],'Save all your English notes to the cloud — never lose progress.','Cloud computing allows access to data from any device, anywhere.','My English study materials are on the cloud — accessible globally.','Cloud migration is the top IT priority for enterprises worldwide.','Cloud service providers are bound by strict data protection regulations.','On the cloud = safer than on your laptop that might crash!',"'Cloud' (weather: white cloud in sky). 'Cloud computing' = online storage and processing. Very different contexts."),
];

