const natureWords = [
  w(881,'nature','प्रकृति','the physical world including plants, animals, and landscapes','/ˈneɪtʃər/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['environment','world','earth','wildlife'],['city','urban','artificial'],'Nature is the best teacher — observe and learn.','Nature vocabulary: mountain, river, forest, ocean, desert, sky.','By nature, I am curious — that\'s why I love learning English.','Nature-based tourism is the fastest-growing segment of travel.','Environmental laws protect nature from human exploitation.','Nature walks clear your mind — take a break, come back stronger!',"'Nature' (the natural world), 'by nature' (naturally: she is by nature very kind), 'nature vs. nurture' (debate)."),
  w(882,'environment','पर्यावरण','the natural world; the surroundings in which you live','/ɪnˈvaɪrənmənt/','Nature & Environment','noun','A2',['surroundings','ecosystem','habitat','nature'],['urban','artificial','controlled'],'A positive learning environment helps you absorb English faster.','Protect the environment — reduce, reuse, recycle.','The environment of this course is supportive and motivating.','Corporate environmental responsibility is now a business priority.','Environmental regulations require companies to minimize pollution.','Create a positive study environment — quiet, organized, inspiring!',"'Environment' (nature context), 'work environment' (office culture), 'learning environment' (classroom). Three uses!"),
  w(883,'climate','जलवायु','the typical weather conditions in an area','/ˈklaɪmɪt/','Nature & Environment','noun','A2',['weather','temperature','conditions'],['vacuum','indoor','controlled'],'Climate change is the biggest challenge facing our generation.','The climate in Bengaluru is perfect — not too hot or cold.','Business climate = market conditions. Economic climate = economic conditions.','Climate commitments drive corporate sustainability reporting globally.','Climate law is an emerging field of environmental jurisprudence.','Climate of fear vs. climate of opportunity — which do you choose?',"'Climate' (weather patterns over time). 'Weather' (day-to-day). 'Climate change' = long-term global shift."),
  w(884,'water','जल / पानी','the liquid that falls as rain and fills rivers and oceans','/ˈwɔːtər/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['liquid','H2O','river','ocean'],['fire','drought','desert'],'Water is essential for all life on Earth — protect it.','Water scarcity is a growing global challenge this century.','Information flows like water — English channels it everywhere.','Water conservation programs are now required by law for industries.','Access to clean water is a fundamental human right.','Still water runs deep — quiet people often know the most!',"'Water' idioms: 'in hot water' = in trouble, 'water under the bridge' = past issue resolved, 'test the waters' = try carefully.","water","waters","watering","watered","watered"),
  w(885,'sun','सूरज / सूर्य','the star around which the Earth orbits','/sʌn/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['sunshine','solar','daystar'],['moon','night','darkness'],'The sun rises in the east and sets in the west.','Sunlight = energy = positivity = better English learning!','Every day is a new sunrise — a new chance to practice English.','Solar energy is rapidly replacing fossil fuels in power generation.','The sun sets at approximately 6:30 PM during winter months.','Rise with the sun, study with the sun, shine like the sun!',"'The sun' (definite article always used). 'Sunshine' = sunny weather or optimism. 'Sunny' = adjective (sunny day)."),
  w(886,'rain','बारिश / वर्षा','water that falls from clouds in drops','/reɪn/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['shower','downpour','drizzle'],['sun','drought','dry weather'],'Listen to rain sounds while studying — very calming.','Rain or shine — I practice English every single day.','Come rain or come shine — very common English idiom = always.','The rainy season increases agricultural productivity in India.','The rainfall data was presented as evidence in the environmental case.','It\'s raining outside — perfect weather for English study inside!',"'Rain' idioms: 'right as rain' = perfectly fine, 'rain check' = postpone, 'save for a rainy day' = save money.","rain","rains","raining","rained","rained"),
  w(887,'tree','पेड़','a large plant with a trunk and branches','/triː/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['plant','oak','palm','pine'],['stump','desert','pavement'],'A tree that bends in the wind doesn\'t break — be flexible.','Tree plantation is a key corporate sustainability initiative.','Knowledge is a tree — English is the fruit it produces.','The deforestation rate threatens biodiversity in the Amazon.','The tree was protected under the Forest Conservation Act.','Plant a tree today — for the planet and for your children!',"'Tree' idioms: 'bark up the wrong tree' = look in the wrong place, 'family tree' = genealogy chart."),
  w(888,'mountain','पहाड़','a very high area of land','/ˈmaʊntən/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['hill','peak','summit','ridge'],['valley','plain','sea'],'English fluency is a mountain — climb one step daily.','Mountains are dangerous but beautiful — just like challenging grammar!','The journey to mountain top = the journey to fluency. Both worth it.','Mountain tourism is a growing economic sector in Himachal Pradesh.','The mountain range forms a natural border between the two countries.','Make a mountain out of a molehill = exaggerate a small problem!',"'Mountain' idioms: 'move mountains' = achieve great things, 'mountain of work' = huge amount, 'if the mountain won\'t...' = adapt to reality."),
  w(889,'river','नदी','a large body of water that flows to the sea','/ˈrɪvər/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['stream','creek','waterway'],['desert','mountain','ocean'],'Rivers carry water to the sea — English carries ideas to the world.','The Ganga, Yamuna, and Godavari are sacred rivers in India.','Life is a river — keep flowing, don\'t stagnate.','River pollution is monitored under the National River Conservation Plan.','The river dispute was adjudicated by an interstate tribunal.','Flow like a river — steady, persistent, unstoppable! That\'s English!',"'River' flows into the sea. 'Stream' = smaller. 'Creek' = even smaller. 'Brook' = tiny, babbling stream."),
  w(890,'ocean','समुद्र / महासागर','a very large body of saltwater covering Earth','/ˈoʊʃən/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['sea','deep water','marine'],['land','continent','desert'],'English vocabulary is an ocean — dive in every day!','The ocean absorbs 90% of the heat from climate change.','There\'s an ocean of opportunity for English speakers in India.','Ocean freight is the backbone of global trade and commerce.','Maritime law governs activities in the ocean and international waters.','Bro, knowledge is like the ocean — always more to explore!',"'Ocean' vs. 'sea': Oceans are larger. 5 oceans: Pacific, Atlantic, Indian, Arctic, Southern."),
  w(891,'forest','जंगल / वन','a large area covered with trees','/ˈfɒrɪst/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['jungle','woods','woodland'],['desert','city','plain'],'Can\'t see the wood for the trees = can\'t see the big picture.','The Amazon forest is often called the lungs of the Earth.','Lost in the forest of grammar? Focus on one rule at a time.','Forest carbon credits are becoming important business assets.','Deforestation rates are monitored by the Forest Survey of India.','Dense forest of vocabulary? No problem — we go one word at a time!',"'Forest' (large, dense trees). 'Wood/Woods' (smaller, informal). 'Jungle' (tropical, dense). All mean wooded area."),
  w(892,'air','हवा / वायु','the mixture of gases around Earth','/ɛər/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['atmosphere','breeze','oxygen','wind'],['water','earth','vacuum'],'Fresh air clears your mind for better English learning.','Air quality in metro cities is a growing health concern.','Put it in the air — it\'s in the atmosphere — it\'s everywhere.','Air travel accounts for 2.5% of global carbon emissions.','Air pollution levels exceeded safe limits in 12 major cities.','Take a breath of fresh air — then come back and study!',"'Air' idioms: 'up in the air' = uncertain, 'clear the air' = resolve misunderstanding, 'on air' = broadcasting.","air","airs","airing","aired","aired"),
  w(893,'weather','मौसम','the conditions of the atmosphere at a particular time','/ˈweðər/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['climate','conditions','forecast'],['indoor','controlled'],'Weather is the most common conversation starter in English!','"What\'s the weather like?" — most used English small talk question.','Whatever the weather, practice English every day — no excuses!','Weather patterns are key indicators for agricultural planning.','Severe weather warnings are issued by the Meteorological Department.','Small talk: "Nice weather today, isn\'t it?" — now you know!',"'Weather' (current conditions). 'Climate' (long-term patterns). 'Weather forecast' = prediction. 'Under the weather' = sick."),
  w(894,'pollution','प्रदूषण','harmful substances in the environment','/pəˈluːʃən/','Nature & Environment','noun','B1',['contamination','toxicity','dirt'],['clean air','purity','freshness'],'Pollution of bad grammar habits — fix them now!','Air pollution reduces cognitive function and learning capacity.','Polluted thinking with negativity = poor English learning results.','Industrial pollution regulations are increasingly strict globally.','Pollution above permitted limits was grounds for factory closure.','Mental pollution = negative self-talk. Detox with positive affirmations!',"'Pollution' types: air, water, soil, noise, light, plastic. All caused by human activity. All harmful."),
  w(895,'sustainability','स्थिरता / टिकाऊपन','the ability to be maintained at a certain level over time','/səˌsteɪnəˈbɪlɪti/','Nature & Environment','noun','B2',['durability','long-term','eco-friendly'],['waste','excess','depletion'],'Sustainable English learning = consistent practice every day.','Sustainability reports are now mandatory for large companies.','My sustainability goal: English fluency maintained for life.','ESG (Environmental, Social, Governance) drives corporate sustainability.','The company\'s sustainability commitments were audited independently.','Daily English practice = sustainable fluency. Short-term cramming ≠ sustainable!',"'Sustainable Development Goals' (SDGs) = 17 UN goals for 2030. Very important in professional English."),
  w(896,'recycle','पुनर्चक्रण करना','to convert waste into reusable material','/ˌriːˈsaɪkəl/','Nature & Environment','verb','A2',['reuse','repurpose','conserve'],['waste','throw away','pollute'],'Recycle knowledge: review old vocabulary to reinforce learning.','Paper, plastic, glass, metal — know how to recycle each.','Recycle your English mistakes into learning opportunities.','Companies with recycling programs reduce waste costs significantly.','The municipality introduced mandatory recycling regulations in 2023.','Recycle your old notes into flashcards — sustainable learning!',"'Reduce, Reuse, Recycle' = 3Rs of sustainability. 'Upcycle' = create something better from waste.","recycle","recycles","recycling","recycled","recycled"),
  w(897,'animal','जानवर / पशु','a living creature that is not a plant','/ˈænɪməl/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['creature','beast','wildlife','species'],['plant','human (sometimes)','mineral'],'Animal sounds in English: dog=bark, cat=meow, cow=moo.','Learning animal vocabulary helps in reading and nature discussions.','Animal metaphors: a lion in the meeting, fox-like thinking.','Animal husbandry contributes significantly to India\'s rural economy.','Animal cruelty is punishable under the Prevention of Cruelty Act.','Bro, which animal best describes your personality? I\'m a lion — roar!',"Animal vocabulary: domestic (dog, cat, cow), wild (lion, tiger, elephant), ocean (shark, whale, dolphin)."),
  w(898,'plant','पौधा / लगाना','a living organism (tree, flower, grass); to put a seed in soil','/plɑːnt/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['flower','tree','vegetation','herb'],['animal','mineral','artificial'],'Plant seeds of vocabulary daily — harvest fluency later.','Plant a garden and learn all the English plant names!','Plant the idea of English in your mind — let it grow.','Vertical plant factories are the future of urban food production.','The environmental law requires companies to plant 10 trees per acre cleared.','Plant one English word today → reap fluency for life!',"'Plant' as noun (a flower is a plant) and verb (plant a tree, plant an idea, plant evidence). Multiple meanings.","plant","plants","planting","planted","planted"),
  w(899,'sky','आकाश','the space above Earth with clouds, sun, and stars','/skaɪ/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['heavens','atmosphere','space'],['ground','earth','basement'],'The sky is the limit for your English learning journey!','Blue sky thinking = creative, unrestricted ideas. Used in business.','Look up at the sky and say your English sentences aloud!','Sky-high expectations require ground-level consistent effort.','Sky conditions are monitored continuously by aviation authorities.','Sky\'s the limit bro — 75 days to English fluency!',"'Sky is the limit' = no limit. 'Sky-high' = very high (prices, expectations). 'Blue-sky thinking' = creative brainstorming."),
  w(900,'earth','पृथ्वी / मिट्टी','the planet we live on; soil','/ɜːrθ/','Nature & Environment','noun','A1',['world','globe','soil','ground'],['sky','space','heaven'],'Protect planet Earth — it\'s our only home.','Down to earth = practical, not arrogant. Great English expression!','The Earth is approximately 4.5 billion years old.','The Earth Summit shaped global environmental policy frameworks.','Earth Day is celebrated on April 22nd every year worldwide.','Down to earth = my kind of person — practical and real!',"'Earth' (the planet), 'earth' (soil/ground), 'down to earth' (practical/humble). 'Move heaven and earth' = do everything possible."),
];

