const sportsWords = [
  w(901,'cricket','क्रिकेट','a popular bat-and-ball sport in India','/ˈkrɪkɪt/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['sport','game','match'],['football','hockey','swimming'],'India won the 2024 T20 World Cup — celebration time!','Cricket vocabulary: bat, ball, wicket, over, run, out, boundary.','Life is like cricket: sometimes out, but get back to bat!','Cricket and English share one thing: India is passionate about both.','The cricket board regulates all international matches and tournaments.','Bro, cricket match tonight — India vs Australia — must watch!',"Cricket positions: batsman, bowler, wicketkeeper, fielder. Shots: sweep, drive, cut, pull, hook."),
  w(902,'football','फुटबॉल','the world\'s most popular ball sport played with feet','/ˈfʊtbɔːl/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['soccer','sport','match'],['cricket','hockey','tennis'],'Football = "soccer" in America. Remember this difference!','Cristiano Ronaldo speaks English — motivation to learn!','Football vocabulary: goal, pass, tackle, penalty, offside, captain.','Football sponsorship is one of the largest advertising channels globally.','FIFA regulations govern all international football competitions.','Bro, football match tonight — ManCity vs Liverpool!',"'Football' = soccer (globally). 'American football' = NFL sport. In India, 'football' = soccer usually."),
  w(903,'game','खेल','an activity with rules played for fun or competition','/ɡeɪm/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['match','contest','sport','play'],['work','study','reality'],'English learning is a game — play it with joy every day.','Game theory applies to business negotiations and strategy.','Language learning is a long game — consistent wins.','Game-changing products disrupt entire industries overnight.','The game of cricket has been played in India since the 18th century.','Game on! Day 1 of English fluency journey starts now!',"'Game' (sport/play), 'game-changing' (revolutionary), 'game theory' (economics), 'on your game' = performing well."),
  w(904,'win','जीतना','to succeed in a competition or achieve a goal','/wɪn/','Sports & Games','verb','A1',['succeed','triumph','beat','prevail'],['lose','fail','draw','forfeit'],'Win every practice session by completing all 50 questions.','It\'s not about winning but about learning and growing.','Every day I practice, I win — against my yesterday self.','Win-win solutions create value for all negotiating parties.','The winning team is rewarded with a trophy and medal.','Win the day — study English, practice, review. Done!',"'Win-win' = both sides benefit. 'Winning streak' = consecutive wins. 'Win over' = persuade someone.","win","wins","winning","won","won"),
  w(905,'lose','हारना','to fail to win; to no longer have something','/luːz/','Sports & Games','verb','A1',['fail','defeat','fall'],['win','succeed','find'],'Lose a battle, win the war — short-term failure, long-term success.','You\'ll never lose if you never stop learning.','I lose nothing by making mistakes — I gain experience.','Losing market share to competitors is a serious business threat.','The defendant lost the case on grounds of insufficient evidence.','Bro, I lost at chess but learned 3 new English words — who won?',"'Lose' vs. 'Loose': Lose (verb = fail to win). Loose (adjective = not tight). VERY commonly confused!","lose","loses","losing","lost","lost"),
  w(906,'team','दल / टीम','a group of people playing or working together','/tiːm/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['group','squad','crew'],['individual','solo','rival'],'Team English: practice with friends for best results.','My team at work motivates me to speak English confidently.','English course team: teacher + students + content = success team.','High-performance teams communicate clearly and collaborate effectively.','The team captain leads the group both on and off the field.','Team player = someone who works well with others. Be one!',"'Team player' is one of the most common phrases in job interviews. 'Teamwork makes the dream work' = popular saying."),
  w(907,'score','स्कोर / अंक','the number of points earned in a game or test','/skɔːr/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['points','marks','tally'],['zero','nil','blank'],'What\'s your score in today\'s practice test?','High score = evidence of mastery. Low score = map to improvement.','My daily test score improves every week — consistency works!','Net Promoter Score (NPS) measures customer loyalty for businesses.','The score was 3-2 in favor of the home team.','Score 100% in today\'s test — try it! You can do it!',"'Score' (points in game/test), 'settle a score' (get revenge), 'score!' (informal: great!), 'score a goal' (football).","score","scores","scoring","scored","scored"),
  w(908,'champion','चैंपियन / विजेता','a person or team that has won a competition','/ˈtʃæmpiən/','Sports & Games','noun','A2',['winner','victor','title-holder'],['loser','runner-up','beginner'],'You will be a champion of English after 75 days!','Champions are not born — they are made through daily effort.','Day 1 champion: complete all 50 practice questions today.','Championship mindset = preparation + consistency + resilience.','The champion defended their title for three consecutive years.','Champion = someone who doesn\'t stop when it gets hard — be one!',"'Champion' (sports winner), 'champion a cause' (advocate for something), 'champion' = verb: I champion this idea.","champion","champions","championing","championed","championed"),
  w(909,'practice','अभ्यास','repeated activity to improve skill','/ˈpræktɪs/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['training','drill','rehearsal'],['theory','knowledge','concept'],'Perfect practice makes perfect — but imperfect practice is better than none!','Practice speaking English in front of a mirror for 5 minutes.','My practice regime: 1 hour vocabulary, 30 minutes speaking daily.','Practice management systems help professionals organize client work.','Legal practitioners are required to maintain proper case records.','Practice like a champion today — 50 questions, no skip!',"'Practice' (American): both noun and verb. British: 'practise' (verb), 'practice' (noun). Common confusion.","practice","practices","practicing","practiced","practiced"),
  w(910,'competition','प्रतियोगिता','a contest where people try to be better than each other','/ˌkɒmpɪˈtɪʃən/','Sports & Games','noun','A2',['contest','rivalry','tournament'],['cooperation','collaboration','surrender'],'Competition drives excellence — embrace it, don\'t fear it.','Job market competition makes English fluency non-negotiable.','My only real competition: my yesterday self. Beat it today!','Competitive analysis helps businesses understand their market position.','Healthy competition in the workplace fosters innovation and growth.','The real competition is within — improve yourself daily!',"'Competition' (event: enter a competition), 'competition' (rivalry: face competition). 'Competitive' = adjective: competitive market."),
  w(911,'player','खिलाड़ी','a person who plays a sport or game','/ˈpleɪər/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['athlete','sportsperson','participant'],['spectator','coach','referee'],'Be a team player — collaborate, don\'t compete with colleagues.','Key player = the most important person in a team or negotiation.','I am a player in the global English-speaking world now!','Identifying key players in an industry is essential for business strategy.','The player was suspended for violating fair play regulations.','You\'re a player in your own success story — play well!',"'Player' (sports), 'key player' (business = important person), 'team player' (someone collaborative). All very common."),
  w(912,'sport','खेल / क्रीड़ा','an athletic activity requiring skill or physical effort','/spɔːrt/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['game','activity','athletics'],['work','study','art'],'Sport vocabulary: compete, train, win, lose, team, score, match.','Cricket is India\'s religion, not just a sport.','English is the sport of the mind — compete with yourself daily.','Sports sponsorship is a multi-billion dollar global industry.','Sports law covers contracts, doping violations, and competition rules.','Sports + English = double win for career and health!',"'Sport' (British) = one sport. 'Sports' (American) = one or many. 'Sportsmanship' = playing fairly and graciously."),
  w(913,'exercise','व्यायाम / अभ्यास','physical activity done to improve health or skill','/ˈeksərsaɪz/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['workout','activity','training'],['rest','laziness','sedentary'],'English exercise: translate 30 sentences Hindi→English right now.','Physical exercise boosts brain function for better language learning.','Mental exercise: grammar + vocabulary. Physical: walk + yoga.','Corporate wellness programs include physical exercise and mental breaks.','Exercise routines must be adapted to individual health conditions.','Exercise your English every day — minimum 1 hour. No excuses!',"'Exercise' in fitness (gym exercise) and education (grammar exercises). Both = practice and repetition for improvement.","exercise","exercises","exercising","exercised","exercised"),
  w(914,'goal','लक्ष्य / गोल','what you aim to achieve; a point scored in sport','/ɡoʊl/','Sports & Games','noun','A1',['aim','target','objective','score'],['failure','drift','aimlessness'],'My goal: speak English fluently without hesitation by Day 75.','Set SMART goals: Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, Timed.','Today\'s goal: 50 practice questions + 20 new vocabulary words.','Goal-setting is the #1 differentiator between success and mediocrity.','The goal of the legislation is to protect consumer rights.','Goal for today: learn 20 words. Can you beat 25? Try!',"'Goal' (football: scoring a goal), 'life goal' (aspiration), 'SMART goal' (business planning). All very common."),
  w(915,'tournament','प्रतियोगिता / टूर्नामेंट','a series of competitions to find the best player or team','/ˈtɔːrnəmənt/','Sports & Games','noun','A2',['championship','contest','series'],['practice','friendly','one-off'],'English fluency tournament: 75 days, 1 winner — you!','Watch cricket tournaments with English commentary — learn naturally.','Every challenge in this course is a mini-tournament round.','E-sports tournaments now attract millions of online viewers.','Tournament regulations ensure fair play and equal opportunity.','You\'re in the English tournament — 75 days to the championship!',"'Tournament' = organized competition with multiple rounds. 'World Cup' = ultimate tournament. 'Draw' = bracket/schedule."),
  w(916,'referee','रेफरी / निर्णायक','an official who enforces rules in a sport','/ˌrefəˈriː/','Sports & Games','noun','B1',['umpire','judge','official','arbitrator'],['player','coach','spectator'],'Grammar is the referee of English — follow the rules.','The referee is always right — same in English grammar rules!','Your inner referee: review your writing for errors before sending.','Referees in business negotiations ensure fairness and process integrity.','The referee\'s decision is final and cannot be challenged by players.','Bad grammar? The referee (editor) will flag it — fix it!',"'Referee' (football/boxing). 'Umpire' (cricket/tennis). 'Judge' (gymnastics/boxing scored events). All officials.","referee","referees","refereeing","refereed","refereed"),
  w(917,'trophy','ट्रॉफी / पुरस्कार','a prize for winning a competition','/ˈtroʊfi/','Sports & Games','noun','A2',['prize','award','cup','medal'],['defeat','failure','loss'],'English fluency certificate = your trophy after 75 days!','Trophy = symbol of achievement. Your English certificate = your trophy.','Display your English achievements like a trophy — be proud!','Trophy clients are prestigious companies that validate your business.','The trophy was presented at the annual sports day ceremony.','Day 75 = trophy day. Start earning it from Day 1 today!',"'Trophy wife/husband' = derogatory. 'Trophy client' = prestigious customer. Careful with context!"),
  w(918,'medal','पदक / मेडल','a flat piece of metal given as a prize','/ˈmedl/','Sports & Games','noun','A2',['award','prize','honor'],['defeat','fail','disqualify'],'Gold, silver, bronze — English has 3 levels too: good, better, fluent.','Gold medal English = error-free, confident, native-like speaking.','Every vocabulary word learned = adding a medal to your collection.','Olympic gold medals are worth approximately $820 each in metals.','The medal ceremony was conducted according to IOC protocols.','Day 75 medal: Certificate of English Fluency. Go earn it!',"'Gold medal' (1st), 'silver medal' (2nd), 'bronze medal' (3rd). 'Medal of honor' = highest military honor."),
  w(919,'athlete','खिलाड़ी / एथलीट','a person who is good at sports','/ˈæθliːt/','Sports & Games','noun','A2',['sportsperson','competitor','player'],['spectator','coach','fan'],'Language learner = mental athlete. Train daily, recover, repeat.','Athletes dedicate years to mastery — same mindset for English.','Think like an athlete: train (study), compete (speak), review (improve).','Athlete endorsements drive millions in sports marketing revenue.','Amateur athletes are protected from exploitation under sports law.','Train like an athlete: grammar = strength, vocabulary = endurance!',"'Athlete' (general). 'Sprinter' (speed), 'marathon runner' (endurance), 'gymnast' (flexibility). Specific types."),
  w(920,'fitness','तंदुरुस्ती','the state of being physically healthy and strong','/ˈfɪtnəs/','Sports & Games','noun','A2',['health','strength','stamina','wellness'],['weakness','illness','lethargy'],'English fitness test: can you hold a 5-minute conversation? Try!','Physical and mental fitness go hand in hand for peak performance.','English fitness = vocabulary strength + grammar accuracy + speaking speed.','Corporate fitness programs reduce healthcare costs by 30% annually.','Fitness for duty assessments are required for safety-critical roles.','Mental fitness challenge: memorize 10 new words daily for 75 days!',"'Fitness' (physical health), 'fitness for purpose' (suitable for the job), 'fitness test' (assessment). All important."),
];

