const personalityWords = [
  w(941,'honest','ईमानदार','always telling the truth','/ˈɒnɪst/','Personality & Character','adjective','A2',['truthful','sincere','genuine'],['dishonest','lying','deceptive'],'Be honest about your English level — that\'s how you grow.','Honesty in interviews: only claim skills you actually have.','I am honest about my mistakes — that\'s why I improve fast.','Honest communication builds trust in professional relationships.','The honest testimony of the witness was pivotal in the verdict.','An honest hour of practice > 5 dishonest hours of half-attention!',"'Honest' (truthful), 'honest mistake' (unintentional error), 'to be honest/honestly' = starting a frank statement."),
  w(942,'kind','दयालु','caring about others and wanting to help them','/kaɪnd/','Personality & Character','adjective','A1',['caring','generous','compassionate','warm'],['cruel','mean','harsh'],'Be kind to yourself — learning takes time.','Kind feedback helps people improve faster than harsh criticism.','My English teacher is so kind — explains until I understand.','A kind workplace culture attracts and retains top talent.','The judge showed remarkable kindness in considering the circumstances.','Be kind — always. It costs nothing and means everything!',"'Kind' (adjective: kind person), 'kind' (noun: what kind? = what type?). Two different words, same spelling."),
  w(943,'brave','साहसी / बहादुर','having the courage to face danger or difficulty','/breɪv/','Personality & Character','adjective','A2',['courageous','bold','fearless','daring'],['cowardly','timid','afraid'],'Be brave — speak English even when afraid of mistakes.','Brave action: raise your hand in the meeting and speak English.','It takes bravery to start from zero — you\'re brave!','Brave leadership means making hard decisions with integrity.','The brave actions of the plaintiff were recognized by the court.','Brave = speaking English in front of everyone despite fear. Do it!',"'Brave' (adjective), 'bravely' (adverb), 'bravery' (noun). 'Brave face' = hiding your real emotions."),
  w(944,'smart','होशियार / बुद्धिमान','intelligent and quick to understand','/smɑːrt/','Personality & Character','adjective','A1',['intelligent','clever','sharp','bright'],['dumb','foolish','slow'],'Work smart, not just hard — apply learning efficiently.','Smart English learning: focus on high-frequency words first.','Smart professionals invest in both technical and English skills.','Smart goals (Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, Time-bound) drive success.','The smart contract was executed automatically on blockchain network.','Study smart: understand the concept, then practice application!',"'Smart' (intelligent), 'smart device' (connected to internet), 'dress smart' (dress formally). Three meanings!"),
  w(945,'patient','धैर्यवान','able to wait calmly without getting upset','/ˈpeɪʃənt/','Personality & Character','adjective','A2',['calm','tolerant','persevering'],['impatient','rushed','frustrated'],'Be patient with your progress — fluency is a marathon.','A patient teacher changes a student\'s life forever.','I was impatient at first, but patience made the difference.','Patient capital from investors enables long-term business growth.','The court was patient in hearing all submissions carefully.','Patient = person in hospital. Patient = calm/tolerant. Same word!',"'Patient' (adjective: calm), 'patient' (noun: hospital patient). Two completely different meanings, same word."),
  w(946,'determined','दृढ़ संकल्पी','having made a firm decision to do something','/dɪˈtɜːrmɪnd/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['resolute','committed','driven','focused'],['indecisive','weak','undetermined'],'I am determined to complete all 75 days without missing one.','Determined students outperform talented but lazy ones — always.','Determination + daily practice = English fluency. Formula guaranteed.','Determined employees who set clear goals outperform their peers.','The court determined that the evidence was insufficient for conviction.','Day 1, Day 15, Day 30 — still determined? Then Day 75 is yours!',"'Determined' (adjective: very committed). 'Determination' (noun). 'Determine' (verb: to decide or calculate)."),
  w(947,'creative','रचनात्मक','having new and original ideas','/kriˈeɪtɪv/','Personality & Character','adjective','A2',['innovative','imaginative','artistic'],['conventional','boring','uncreative'],'Creative English learning: use words in songs, poems, stories.','Creative thinking is the most valued 21st-century workplace skill.','Create mnemonics creatively — they help vocabulary stick forever.','Creative industries contribute significantly to the knowledge economy.','Creative freedom is often contractually guaranteed for artists.','Be creative with English — write songs, tell stories, make mnemonics!',"'Creative' (adjective), 'creativity' (noun), 'creatively' (adverb), 'create' (verb). All from the same root word."),
  w(948,'ambitious','महत्वाकांक्षी','having a strong desire to succeed','/æmˈbɪʃəs/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['driven','goal-oriented','aspiring'],['lazy','complacent','aimless'],'Be ambitious — English fluency is achievable in 75 days!','Ambitious goals require ambitious action — study 2 hours daily.','My most ambitious goal: speak English like a native speaker.','Ambitious project timelines require efficient resource allocation.','The company\'s ambitious expansion plan was approved at the AGM.','Be ambitious! C1 level in 75 days? Why not? Set the goal!',"'Ambitious' (positive: driven), but sometimes used negatively if someone is too aggressively ambitious."),
  w(949,'disciplined','अनुशासित','behaving in a controlled way; following rules','/ˈdɪsɪplɪnd/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['organized','systematic','structured'],['undisciplined','chaotic','random'],'Disciplined daily practice beats intense occasional effort.','Most successful people are disciplined about their daily routines.','Disciplined English study: same time, same place, every day.','Disciplined teams deliver consistent results and meet deadlines.','The soldier was disciplined for violating the code of conduct.','Discipline = freedom. Disciplined practice = freedom from fear of English!',"'Discipline' (noun: the quality), 'disciplined' (adjective), 'discipline' (verb: to punish or train). Three uses."),
  w(950,'reliable','भरोसेमंद','consistently good and dependable','/rɪˈlaɪəbəl/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['dependable','trustworthy','consistent'],['unreliable','inconsistent','undependable'],'Be a reliable English learner — practice every single day.','Reliable employees are the backbone of any successful organization.','This English course is reliable — consistent quality, proven results.','Reliable supply chains are critical for manufacturing companies.','Reliable testimony from the witness strengthened the prosecution case.','Reliability = your personal brand. Build it one promise at a time!',"'Reliable' (person/system can be counted on). 'Reliable source' = trustworthy information. 'Reliability' = noun form."),
  w(951,'flexible','लचीला / अनुकूलनीय','willing to change and adapt to new situations','/ˈfleksɪbəl/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['adaptable','versatile','accommodating'],['rigid','inflexible','stubborn'],'Be flexible with your English learning methods.','Flexible working hours improve work-life balance for employees.','Flexible thinking: switch between formal and informal English easily.','Business flexibility allows companies to pivot when markets change.','The flexible sentencing guidelines allow judges appropriate discretion.','Flexible = tree in wind. Rigid = dry twig that breaks!',"'Flexible' (adaptable person/schedule). 'Flexibility' (noun). 'Inflexible' = cannot adapt. Office: 'flex hours' = flexible time."),
  w(952,'confident','आत्मविश्वासी','feeling sure of yourself and your abilities','/ˈkɒnfɪdənt/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['self-assured','sure','bold','certain'],['insecure','doubtful','timid'],'I was not confident in English — Day 1. Day 75: unstoppable.','Confident body language: straight posture, eye contact, clear voice.','Fake confidence until it becomes real — it works!','Confident communication is the most sought-after professional skill.','The confident witness delivered testimony without hesitation.','Talk to yourself in English — builds confidence quickly!',"'Confident' (adjective). 'Confidence' (noun). 'Confidently' (adverb). Build all three through daily practice."),
  w(953,'loyal','वफ़ादार / निष्ठावान','faithful to a person, organization, or cause','/ˈlɔɪəl/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['faithful','dedicated','devoted'],['disloyal','traitor','unfaithful'],'Be loyal to your English learning commitment — never give up.','Loyal customers are worth 5x more than new customers to a business.','I am loyal to this 75-day journey — completing every single day.','Customer loyalty programs reward repeat customers with discounts.','The employee showed exemplary loyalty during the company\'s difficult period.','Loyalty to yourself = completing what you started. Day 1 to Day 75!',"'Loyal' (person), 'loyal customer' (business), 'loyalty program' = reward scheme for regular customers."),
  w(954,'generous','उदार / दानी','happy to give more than is expected','/ˈdʒenərəs/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['giving','liberal','benevolent'],['stingy','selfish','greedy'],'Be generous with knowledge — share what you learn.','Generous praise for your team\'s good work costs nothing.','This course is generous — 1000 practice questions daily!','Generous bonus structures attract and retain top talent.','The generous donation enabled the construction of 10 rural schools.','Share English knowledge with friends — generosity grows community!',"'Generous' (giving money/time/praise). 'Generosity' (noun). 'Generously' (adverb). Great character trait."),
  w(955,'humble','विनम्र / नम्र','not proud or arrogant; modest about your achievements','/ˈhʌmbəl/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['modest','meek','unassuming'],['arrogant','proud','boastful'],'Stay humble — there\'s always more to learn in English.','Humble leaders listen to their team before making decisions.','Humble beginnings to English fluency — that\'s the best story.','Humility in leadership creates psychologically safe team environments.','Despite great success, the judge remained humble and approachable.','Be humbly confident — know your value but never boast!',"'Humble' (modest), 'humble pie' = forced to admit you were wrong, 'humility' = the quality of being humble."),
  w(956,'punctual','समय का पाबंद','arriving or doing things at the agreed time','/ˈpʌŋktʃuəl/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['on time','prompt','timely'],['late','tardy','delayed'],'Be punctual in your English practice — same time every day.','Punctuality is a key professional virtue respected globally.','Punctual English practice: 7 AM sharp — every single morning.','Punctual delivery builds client trust and business reputation.','The punctual submission of documents ensured the case proceeded.','Early is on time. On time is late. Late is unacceptable!',"'Punctual' (adjective), 'punctuality' (noun), 'punctually' (adverb). Very valued in professional contexts globally."),
  w(957,'responsible','ज़िम्मेदार','having the duty to do something; being able to be trusted','/rɪˈspɒnsɪbəl/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['accountable','reliable','dependable'],['irresponsible','careless','unaccountable'],'Take responsibility for your English practice — no excuses.','Responsible professionals own their mistakes and fix them.','I am responsible for my own English learning — no one else.','Corporate social responsibility (CSR) builds brand reputation.','The company was held responsible for the environmental damage.','Responsible adult = someone who owns their actions. Be one!',"'Responsible for' (in charge of), 'take responsibility' (own your actions), 'responsible' (trustworthy person)."),
  w(958,'passionate','उत्साही / जुनूनी','showing strong enthusiasm or interest','/ˈpæʃənɪt/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['enthusiastic','devoted','eager','fervent'],['indifferent','cold','unenthusiastic'],'I am passionate about learning English — nothing stops me.','Passionate learners outperform talented but disinterested ones.','Passion for English turns study into joy — feel it!','Passionate teams build breakthrough products that change industries.','The passionate advocate moved the jury with compelling arguments.','Passion + Practice + Patience = English Fluency. PPP formula!',"'Passionate about' something. 'Passion project' = work you do out of love. 'Passion' drives all great achievements."),
  w(959,'persistent','दृढ़ / जिद्दी','continuing firmly despite obstacles','/pərˈsɪstənt/','Personality & Character','adjective','B1',['determined','tenacious','consistent'],['quitting','giving up','weak'],'Persistent daily practice = fluency. No other path exists.','Persistent follow-up on job applications gets interviews.','I was persistent — 30 days became 60 became 75 Days Hard English.','Persistent customer outreach builds long-term revenue relationships.','The persistent plaintiff finally received justice after three years.','Persist through Day 10, Day 30, Day 50 — and Day 75 is yours!',"'Persistent' (continuing despite obstacles). 'Persistence' (noun). 'Persist' (verb). All three are important."),
  w(960,'positive','सकारात्मक','optimistic and confident about the future','/ˈpɒzɪtɪv/','Personality & Character','adjective','A2',['optimistic','hopeful','constructive'],['negative','pessimistic','doubtful'],'Stay positive — every mistake is a step toward fluency.','Positive mindset transforms language learning from burden to joy.','Positive English practice: celebrate every new word mastered.','Positive company culture attracts talent and drives innovation.','The test result came back positive — immediate action is required.','Positive thoughts in English: "I can do this!" Say it daily!',"'Positive' (optimistic), 'positive test result' (found what was tested for), 'think positive' = be optimistic."),
];

